The agreement on three credit frameworks of a total value of EUR 400 million to support education, transport and environmental infrastructure as well as energy was signed on Friday in Budapest by Finance Minister János Veres and Marta Gajecka, Vice-President of the European Investment Bank (EIB).
In 2006, the European Investment Bank (EIB) approved a framework of €300 million for Hungarian budget financing of projects in the field of transport and the environment, implemented by the Cohesion Fund, with the parties already signed a loan agreement of €100 million, the now signed agreement concerns the use of the remaining €200 million.
A loan agreement of €150 million is also used for the budgetary financing of education-related projects.
