Holidays are not everywhere.
In Hungary, the holidays are precisely established by law and it has already become a general practice that working days move around holidays, which awaits us less times next year.
There are no unified holidays in the European Union or in America.
The Hungarian legal system distinguishes national and state holidays and working days.
Work days are usually linked to church holidays or important historical events.
We also celebrate the New Year: the last day of the old and the first day of the new year is working holidays - for the New Year already so that people can rest after the New Year.
We have a total of 11 holidays over the year.
National holiday is the 15th of March celebrating the Revolution of 1848 and the 23th of October, the Memorial Day of the Revolution of 1956.
On 20 August we celebrate the foundation of the state, on 1 May work, on 1 and 2 November we remember the deceased relatives and friends.
In addition, there are two-day holidays of Easter, Summer and Christmas.
Since our national, national or religious holidays according to the calendar rarely fall on a weekend, it has become a practice to move the working day in cases that we would only work one day before or after the holiday.
The price for prolonged weekends, however, is that the previous Saturday we stay at workplace and at school.
The time we work on the day that immediately precedes or follows the holiday, has been regulated by the Ministry of Labor in a special decree for many years.
The legislation shall apply equally to all employers and employees employed by them, to public employees and to persons in public service.
It does not apply, however, to companies and institutions that are in operation without interruption or with regard to their destination operate even in working days.
This year there will be a change in the working schedule just around the holidays at the end of the year: from December 24 life in the country will almost stop, since according to the previous experience most people "work" in advance the days between Christmas and New Year, or thus take advantage of the saved holiday.
In the next year, some of our holidays falls in the middle, respectively, to the end of the week, so the work day movements will be less than this year.
For the first time, the calendar is converted around the work holiday, so that the workers can then stay at home for four days of taste.
Saturday 26th April will be a working day, so on the contrary, Friday 2th May will be a day of rest.
The next move is related to the holiday of 23 October: on Saturday 18 October will work instead of Friday 24.
The end of the year, however, the next year will be able to take place completely in the sign of holidays, because from December 24 they will have almost everywhere nonstop holidays even though New Year's Eve falls on Wednesday.
