What insurance is suitable for me?
The car insurance that protects the driver in the event of an accident represents a significant expenditure that depends on various factors such as age, state, gender, length of holding the driver’s license, the type of vehicle to be insured or its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing an appropriate car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, we need to clarify what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insurer.
This obligation takes the form of an insurance contract, which provides that the insurance company receives the agreed insurance amount in a certain amount for taking care of the payment of damages in the event of an insurance event.
Insurance is the price of the insurance that is determined with regard to different factors, such as age, state, gender, length of driving license, type of vehicle that is insured or its use, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so the greater the likelihood of an accident, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both persons over the age of 25 and women must pay lower insurance fees, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
Similarly, on the basis of the checks, insurance companies concluded that married persons suffer less accidents than free drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of driving, and thus the likelihood of having an accident.
The increase in frequency increases the probability.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when setting the price of insurance.
Therefore, the driver must well study the situation to choose such insurance that best corresponds to his insurer profile.
We will show you the most important variable for the choice of that or that type of insurance, which in addition to meeting the type of insurance, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under twenty-five years of age face a variety of disadvantages such as low driving experience and short driving license holding when they want to negotiate insurance at an affordable price.
Although ideal for good coverage is insurance against all risks, there are even cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can choose insurance against all risks with a discount of insurance so that they get insurance coverage for all risks, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would require the participation of the customer in the payment of the insurance event.
“The part of the payment of the insurance event that the client will provide will be determined in advance when determining the price of the insurance will be higher, the lower the co-participation would be,” explains Luis Noguera, the chief executive of First Europe in Spain, an online insurance broker.
Another option is the insurance extended to other operators so that the client is insured against damages caused to other persons, but not against damages on his own car.
In addition, he would be insured against theft, fire and vehicle loss.
the recommendation.
If you are under twenty-five years of age, try to be careful and avoid accidents as much as possible, as it will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce insurance fees in the future.
The bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the insurance company has.
On the contrary, malus is an increase in the aforementioned basic rate.
“Bonus and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profits.
If the insurance company had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus,” Noguera explains.
After exceeding the twenty-five-year limit, drivers get it easier when they go to contract insurance, as the customer risk index is reduced to them, thanks to the acquired experience.
For this reason, it is most recommended to negotiate insurance against all risks with a discount.
“Young people can usually not take advantage of the previously acquired experience at the time an accident occurs, and not even when driving,” the director of the European company in Spain assures and adds that most of the accidents occur in the second year of conduct, when the “newman’s fear” has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but still has no children, it is better to negotiate insurance against all risks, if his economic situation allows it.
Families with children are considered by insurance companies as clients with the lowest risk index and therefore their preferences will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks with a discount of the insurance fee (which could be 300 euros) or with a high bonus, insurance extended to other operators, starting the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
“Their management is more quiet and their purchasing capacity is higher, so they can afford to get the highest discount,” said Luis Noguera.
Pensioners are recommended insurance against all risks with a discount of the insurance fee (which is EUR 150) or insurance extended to other operators if a high bonus has been achieved.
It should be said that car insurance is something important not only because it protects the driver in case of an accident, but also because it represents a significant cost, which is a good reason to properly study the insurance options that would be the most suitable for us given our personal situation.
